&lt;p&gt;The Office of Diversity, Culture, and Inclusion at Columbia University Mailman School of Public Health launched the FACE Forward Speaker Series in the fall of 2021. It features panel discussions with renowned public health experts. Through this series, a variety of guests &amp;ndash; from local policymakers to community organizers to international public health innovators &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;share insights on anti-racist practice and engage in a dialogue with faculty, staff, and students. &lt;a href="https://www.publichealth.columbia.edu/research/office-diversity-culture-and-inclusion/face-forward-speaker-series"&gt;Learn more.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

