&lt;h2&gt;Sustain What?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A Pan-Pacific Music Conversation with Small Island Big Song&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Andy Revkin of the Columbia Climate School in a special hour exploring the nexus of music, Pacific and Indian Ocean culture and climate with the founders of the Small Island Big Song project - BaoBao Chen of Taiwan and Tim Cole of Australia - along with Selina Leem, a spoken-word performer from the Marshall Islands.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Small Island Big Song is a music, film, and live performance project featuring over 100 musicians across 16 island nations of the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Learn more here: https://www.smallislandbigsong.com/&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This event is a bit of a curtain raiser for their March 18 performance at Symphony Space in Manhattan, presented by the World Music Institute.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Send feedback and ideas for future shows to Andy: http://j.mp/sustainwhatfeedback&lt;br /&gt;
