&lt;p&gt;Gỏi cuốn, also known as spring or summer roll, is one of the most iconic Vietnamese dishes traditionally consisting of pork, prawn, vegetables, b&amp;uacute;n (rice vermicelli), and other ingredients wrapped in b&amp;aacute;nh tr&amp;aacute;ng (rice paper wrapper). It is classically dipped in either peanut sauce, fish sauce, or hoisin sauce. Contrary to popular belief, this dish originates from Vietnam and not China.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;APAMSA is especially interested in providing AAPI students with this hands-on opportunity to engage in Vietnamese food and culture due to the organization&amp;rsquo;s relative lack of Southeast Asian representation in the past. Increasing representation of Southeast Asian culture in APAMSA events is one of the current board&amp;rsquo;s biggest goals this year (as well as South Asian culture). This issue also extends far beyond our organization, as educational and economic disparities amongst Southeast Asian Americans are often overlooked. These educational disparities are particularly apparent in medicine, and in the VP&amp;amp;S M1 class there are no fully Southeast Asian students at all. Asian Americans are extremely diverse yet are often grouped together with East Asians viewed as the prototype &amp;ndash; not just by non-AAPI individuals, but also by many Asian Americans too. With this in mind, it is crucial for APAMSA to diversify events and educate students about Southeast Asian culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Board members would prepare fresh ingredients beforehand and split them into containers for each table. Instructions for making the spring roll would be displayed on the classroom&amp;rsquo;s large screen. Attendees would be informed about masking guidelines and told to wash their hands, then they would be able to make their own spring rolls and eat them with dipping sauces we will provide. Dietary restrictions would be assessed via RSVP form and different ingredients/dipping options provided accordingly. We want to cap the attendance at 30 students, but depending on COVID gathering guidelines at the time, we can adjust this number accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

