&lt;h2&gt;&amp;ldquo;Methodologic Innovations in Study Design: A Randomized Selection Trial for Prevention of Chemotherapy Induced Peripheral Neuropathy&amp;rdquo;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MELISSA ACCORDINO, MD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Assistant Professor Department of Medicine&lt;br /&gt;
Medical Hematology &amp;amp; Oncology Columbia University&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This talk will highlight a novel randomized selection design in a phase II trial. The objective of this study was to determine which of three strategies (cryotherapy, compression therapy, placebo) had the highest probability of success in a future phase III study to prevent chemotherapy induced peripheral neuropathy.&lt;/p&gt;
