&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="https://racespacearchitecture.org/"&gt;Race, Space, and Architecture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an open-access curriculum shared of many voices which engages with three questions: What are the spatial contours of capitalism that produce racial hierarchy and injustice? &#8232;What are the inventive repertoires of refusal, resistance, and re-making that are neither reduced to nor exhausted by racial capitalism and how are they specialized? &#8232;How is &amp;lsquo;race&amp;rsquo; configured differently across space, and how can a more expansive understanding of entangled world space broaden our imagination for teaching ​and learning?&lt;/p&gt;
